    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "90 mins sounds doable i guess. what about the bit at the end? once i get to edinburgh i need to grab a bus to my hotel. how much time should i leave between the train arriving and needing to be on that bus? i'm not great with directions so i don't want to be sprinting through the station if i can avoid it.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Leaving a buffer time between the train arriving in Edinburgh Waverley and needing to catch your local bus is crucial, especially if you're not keen on sprinting. I'd suggest aiming for **at least 30 to 45 minutes**. This gives you time to navigate the station, find the correct bus stop, maybe grab a quick snack if you're feeling peckish, and avoid that frantic, panicked scramble.\n\nIf you try to rush, you'll end up looking like a lost traveler, and honestly, that's just an extra headache for the whole journey. It's much better to have a little slack in your schedule, like a well-tended patch of moss in a dark corner—it keeps things from crumbling! Just make sure you check the bus schedule beforehand; sometimes those local transport schedules are as unreliable as a poorly organized pile of old socks.",
